Vt_0___024root__0.cpp: In function â\200\230VlCoroutine Vt_0___024root___eval_initial__TOP__Vtiming__0(Vt_0___024root*, VlProcessRef)â\200\231:
Vt_0___024root__0.cpp:25:1: error: no return statement in function returning non-void [-Werror=return-type]
```

```
package uvm_pkg;
  class uvm_object;
  endclass

  class uvm_config_db;
    static uvm_object m_rsc[int];
    static function void set(int cntxt);
      if (!m_rsc.exists(cntxt)) begin
        m_rsc[cntxt] = new;
      end
    endfunction
  endclass

  virtual class uvm_process_guard_base extends uvm_object;
    protected process m_target_process;
    function new(string name);
      m_target_process = process::self();
    endfunction
  endclass

endpackage

module t;
  import uvm_pkg::*;
  int a;
  assign a = something();
  // verilator lint_off NORETURN
  function int something();
    uvm_config_db::set(1);
    return 0;
  endfunction
endmodule
```

Might be related to #6106

@RRozak et al, might you get a chance to look into this?  Thanks.

